 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-C8-004: Guidance system hardcodes Basin Competition model — 14,137 LOC of DDIS methodology in kernel. PROBLEM: The guidance system spans guidance.rs (7,119 LOC) + methodology.rs (1,715 LOC) + routing.rs (2,879 LOC) + context.rs (2,424 LOC) = 14,137 LOC combined, 17% of the 83,293 LOC kernel. It contains: classify_command() hardcoding braid CLI commands ('guidance', 'bilateral', 'harvest', 'seed', 'witness', 'challenge', 'spec'), Basin competition model (Basin A = DDIS methodology, Basin B = pretrained patterns), COTX routing rules for finding/task/ADR/question categories, default derivation rules referencing 'invariant' and 'adr' artifact types, M(t) methodology score with DDIS-specific telemetry. This is the most C8-violating area of the kernel by LOC. JUSTIFICATION: The guidance system confuses two concerns: (1) the framework for budget-aware context projection and methodology steering (substrate-agnostic), and (2) the DDIS-specific content that flows through the framework (domain-specific). The framework is analogous to a web framework; the DDIS guidance is analogous to a specific web application. Both live in the same module. C8 demands separation. SOLUTION: This is the hardest C8 fix. (1) Extract a GuidanceProvider trait in the kernel with methods for classify_command(), compute_methodology_score(), generate_routing(). (2) Move DDIS-specific implementation to a DDIS guidance plugin or application-layer module. (3) Policy datoms specify which GuidanceProvider to use. The kernel guidance module retains the framework (~3K LOC); DDIS-specific logic moves out (~11K LOC). VERIFICATION: Kernel guidance module contains no string literal referencing 'invariant', 'ADR', 'harvest', or 'bilateral'. DEPENDENCIES: Independent of F-C8-001 (can be done in parallel). The largest single task in the roadmap. Subsumes F-ARCH-001 (guidance module size). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs, methodology.rs, routing.rs, context.rs. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 2. EFFORT: 40h."
